# NIX RUN
Nixpkgs: nixpkgs.nix
Source: https://github.com/NixOS/nix
Description: Run a Nix executable from a flake.
Version: nix --version

## Commands

### Basics
- nix run nixpkgs#hello: Run the 'hello' package directly.

### Essentials
- nix run . : Run the default app defined in the local flake.
- nix run .#app-name: Run a specific app from the local flake.

### Intermediaries
- nix run nixpkgs#cowsay -- "Hello world": Pass arguments to the executable.

### Advanceds
- nix run github:nix-community/home-manager -- switch: Run Home Manager without installing it.

### Uncommons
- nix run --refresh nixpkgs#tool: Force update of the flake registry before running.

## Tips
- Ideal for one-off tasks or testing tools without installation.

## Disclaimers
- Requires the package to have a 'defaultApp' or 'apps' defined in the flake.

## Alternatives
- nix shell: If you need to run multiple different commands from the same package.

